    Fix/startup freeze

[33mcommit a1740fb4776e93181b2ff26cbf6384f89befbbac[m[33m ([m[1;31morigin/fix/startup-freeze[m[33m)[m
Author: google-labs-jules[bot] <161369871+google-labs-jules[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 18 03:21:55 2025 +0000

    feat: Add startup API call caching to avoid rate limits
    
    This commit introduces a new feature to cache the timestamp of the last successful API data fetch. On subsequent startups, the application checks this timestamp. If the last fetch was within the last 5 minutes, it skips the initial data loading to avoid hitting API rate limits.
    
    - A new `app_state.py` module was created to handle persisting the `last_api_fetch_timestamp` to an `app_state.json` file.
    - The startup logic in `main_app.py` was modified to check this timestamp and conditionally skip the initial data fetch, informing the user via the loading screen.
    - The timestamp is updated only after a new successful data fetch.
    
    This change improves the application's robustness and provides a faster startup experience when restarted frequently.

[33mcommit 370562af2e52139494ad9d90f114b4e84345e7ab[m
Author: google-labs-jules[bot] <161369871+google-labs-jules[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 18 03:18:04 2025 +0000

    Fix: Resolve application freeze when displaying alerts
    
    This commit addresses a deadlock issue in the `AlertConsolidator` class that caused the application to freeze when an alert was triggered.
    
    The `_process_alerts` method, running in a background thread, was holding a lock while sleeping (`time.sleep`). This blocked the main thread when it tried to add a new alert via the `add_alert` method, which also needs the same lock, leading to a GUI freeze.
    
    The fix refactors the `_process_alerts` method to ensure that `time.sleep` is called outside the lock's scope. This prevents the deadlock and ensures the main application thread remains responsive.

[33mcommit 99f9795689c67feb9a2890396ce5fd7fb6a1d45b[m
Merge: ad4d365 6b925d0
Author: Paulo Ricardo Bennertz <97566970+PauloBennertz@users.noreply.github.com>
