    Merge pull request #16 from PauloBennertz/fix/startup-freeze
    
    Fix: Prevent application freeze on startup by loading data asynchrono‚Ä¶

[33mcommit 6b925d0b83d99c4e9eb0d3e39e0fc41a32c8d763[m
Author: google-labs-jules[bot] <161369871+google-labs-jules[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 18 03:09:05 2025 +0000

    Fix: Prevent application freeze on startup by loading data asynchronously
    
    The application would freeze upon launch because it was fetching initial data (Binance symbols, CoinGecko mappings) synchronously on the main GUI thread. This blocked the Tkinter event loop from running, making the window unresponsive until the network requests were complete.
    
    This commit refactors the startup sequence to be asynchronous:
    - A new `LoadingWindow` is displayed immediately to provide user feedback.
    - The long-running data fetching operations are moved to a separate background thread.
    - The main application window is only created and displayed after the necessary data has been fetched by the background thread.
    - This ensures the GUI remains responsive and provides a better user experience.

